                <h1>Cookies Teaching Presentation</h1>
                <h1>What are cookies?</h1>
                <p>A cookie is a piece of data that is saved to the user’s computer that contains information about their personal preferences. This cookie is remembered each time the user visits that website.</p>

                <h1>Cookies in PHP</h1>
                <p>setcookie(name, value, time);<br>
                    // name of the cookie<br>
                    // value of the cookie (what is stored on user’s computer)<br>
                    // time when the cookie expires. Specify time or set to ‘0’ to expire when the browser closes.<br>
                    echo $_cookie</p>

                <h1>What Can Cookies Store?</h1>
                <ul>
                    <li>Usernames</li>
                    <li>Passwords</li>
                    <li>Language</li>
                    <li>Country</li>
                    <li>Website layout</li>
                    <li>Time Visited</li>
                    <li>Items added to shopping cart</li>
                    <li>Links clicked on</li>
                </ul>

                <h1>Working Example</h1>
                <p>SET THE COOKIE<br>
                    $value = 'something from somewhere';<br>
                    setcookie("TestCookie", $value);<br>
                    setcookie("TestCookie", $value, time() + 3600); /* expire in 1 hour */<br>
                    setcookie("TestCookie", $value, time() + 3600, "/~rasmus/", "example.com", 1);<br><br>

                    TEST THE COOKIE
                    // Print an individual cookie<br>
                    echo $_COOKIE["TestCookie"];<br>
                    echo $HTTP_COOKIE_VARS["TestCookie"];<br>
                    ?></p>

                <h1>FAQ</h1>
                <p>
                    WHO CAN READ MY COOKIES?<br>
                    Only the website that saved the cookie can read the one it saved to your computer<br><br>

                    WHAT IS A THIRD-PARTY COOKIE?<br>
                    Instead of saving the cookie to your computer, it is now saved to an external database. There is no size limitation, allowing sites to gather more user information.<br><br>

                    WHO CREATES COOKIES?<br>
                    The web developer creates and decides what information a cookie holds.<br><br>

                    ARE COOKIES GOOD OR BAD?<br>
                    Cookies are simply a tool. They were created to improve the user experience, but they can be used for negative reasons as well.
                </p>

                <h1>References</h1>
